        <body>
            <pb n="1"/>
            <p rend="indent(1)">
                <placeName>St Thomas</placeName>
                <date>14 Sept 1857</date>
            </p>
            <p>
                <addressee>Revd Mr Leeser</addressee>
            </p>
            <p>
                <placeName>Phila</placeName>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">My Dr Sir</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">I received your<lb/> favor of the <date>2d Dec</date></p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I was glad to find that<lb/> the congregation of your late<lb/>
                ministry had at length done<lb/> the act of justice that they so<lb/> long defined,
                by sending you<lb/> a copy of the annal of the<lb/> con<add>?</add> so improperly
                    <sic>passid</sic> on<lb/> youâ€”on your part it is your<lb/>
                <hi rend="underline">duty</hi> to attend the Synagogue<lb/> frequently, &amp;
                thereby <add>?</add> to</p>
            <pb n="2"/>
            <p>them that no truce of ill will<lb/> exists.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I have collected 2 years<lb/> subscription from three
                subscribers<lb/> myself being one, &amp; have sold<lb/> the last set of the
                Pentateuch<lb/> &amp; daily &amp; festival prayers, no<lb/> more remainâ€”my Son has
                sold<lb/> the set of the Pentateuch received<lb/> with the Bibles, the money
                for<lb/> which will be paid later. I<lb/> would recommend you to send<lb/> him three
                sets of the Daily &amp;<lb/> Festival prayers, finely bound<lb/> provided you can
                Invoice them<lb/> at about $20 three sets of the</p>
            <pb n="3"/>
            <p><add>?</add> like last &amp; three sets<lb/> of the Pentateuch they are now<lb/>
                &amp; then conquered after</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Enclosed the Bank of St<lb/> Thomas' Bell No 8235 at sight<lb/> on
                    <persName>J C Whitmore</persName> for $42â€”as<lb/> payment in fall for</p>
            <p>1 set of the Pentateuch $12</p>
            <p>1 â€œ of D &amp; F PrayerÂ Â Â Â 12</p>
            <p>2 year subscription of</p>
            <p>3 subscribers to Occident <hi rend="underline">18</hi></p>
            <p>Â Â Â Â Â  Â Â Â Â Â  Â Â Â Â Â $42â€”</p>
            <p>I regret I cannot prevail on<lb/> our people to subscribe, those that<lb/> are
                appertain to my family</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)"><persName>Mrs W</persName> joins in kind regards<lb/> &amp; we beg
                you to also give them<lb/> our friends the <persName>Florences</persName></p>
            <p rend="indent(9)">Yours truly</p>
            <p rend="indent(9)">
                <persName role="author">A. Wolff</persName>
            </p>
            <p>I have collected Â£35 towards<lb/> the testimonial to the late<lb/> Lord Mayor of
                    <placeName>London</placeName>
                <persName>D.<lb/> Solomons</persName></p>
            <pb n="Envelope, Recto"/>
            <p>
                <addressee>Revd Mr I Leeser</addressee>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">
                <placeName>Philada.</placeName>
            </p>
            <pb n="Envelope, Verso"/>
            <p><add>?</add><lb/> forward by <persName>Mr<lb/>
                    <add>?</add></persName> &amp;c</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">
                <hi rend="underline">
                    <persName>D Wolff</persName>
                </hi>
            </p>
